nd make sure they are passing? | Done.\n\nResult:\n- `npm run test:all` passed\n- Ran with:\n  - `DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/foreman`\n- Final marker:\n  - `TEST_ALL_EXIT:0`\n\nAlso fixed test expectations/timeouts needed by workflow change:\n- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-loader.test.ts`\n- `src/lib/__tests__/trd-009-bug-workflow-integration.test.ts`\n- ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"can you run all tests and make sure they are passing?","timestamp":"2026-06-08T15:40:27.824Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5don46_d1e9cc2aabc5":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5don46_d1e9cc2aabc5","importance":5,"narrative":"did you push these changes? | Yes.\n\nPushed to `main`:\n- `00af8997 fix(workflows): route remediation through developer`\n- `c327ed13 test(workflows): align remediation expectations`","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"did you push these changes?","timestamp":"2026-06-08T15:41:06.435Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5eyj9z_88a53fc909c6":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5eyj9z_88a53fc909c6","importance":5,"narrative":"can you pick 1 previously failed task and reset/run it?  Let's see if we can get one to finish end-to-end before throwing everything at foreman. | `retryOnFail` = max retry-loop count for a phase when its verdict is `FAIL`.\n\nExample:\n\n```yaml\n- name: qa\n  verdict: true\n  retryWith: developer\n  retryOnFail: 2\n```\n\nFlow:\n1. Run `qa`.\n2. Parse artifact verdict.\n3. If `qa` says `FAIL`, jump back to `‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"can you pick 1 previously failed task and reset/run it?  Let's see if we can get one to finish end-to-end before throwi‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:16:47.612Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5ezu4a_e0cda6adc7a1":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5ezu4a_e0cda6adc7a1","importance":5,"narrative":"should we limit retry?  Why wouldn't we let it run until completion? | Yes, keep a limit.\n\nWhy not infinite:\n- Prevents runaway spend/time.\n- Avoids loops when root cause is wrong prompt, bad test, env outage, merge conflict, or impossible req.\n- Gives Foreman a clean failure state + artifacts for debug/reset.\n- Stops agents from repeatedly making worse/different changes.\n\nBetter model:\n- Small r‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"should we limit retry?  Why wouldn't we let it run until completion?","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:17:48.322Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5f5afk_8ebbdef49fcd":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5f5afk_8ebbdef49fcd","importance":5,"narrative":"somewhere along the way our seedId changed from foreman-{five digit hex} to a uuid?  When/why did this happen? | Not global. Mixed ID paths.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n- `foreman task create` allocates compact IDs:\n  - `foreman-{5 hex}`\n  - code: `src/cli/commands/task.ts` ‚Üí `allocateTaskId(projectName, existingIds)`\n- Postgres adapter also allocates compact IDs when no `id` supplied:\n  - `src/lib/db/pos‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"somewhere along the way our seedId changed from foreman-{five digit hex} to a uuid?  When/why did this happen?","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:22:02.766Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5f73zj_1b4b0f374451":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5f73zj_1b4b0f374451","importance":5,"narrative":"can you create a bug for this issue?? | Created bug:\n\n- ID: `foreman-70661`\n- Title: `Board-created tasks use UUID IDs instead of compact project IDs`\n- Status: `backlog`\n- Priority: `medium`\n\nNot approved yet.","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"can you create a bug for this issue??","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:23:27.724Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5fhydr_e4d18aced311":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5fhydr_e4d18aced311","importance":5,"narrative":"it appers the board 'cycle' backwards is not working properly?  When I'm on an 'in-progress' task and type 'S' I expect it to go back to 'ready', in reality it doesn't do anything? | Agree. Found bug.\n\nCause:\n- Board columns use `in_progress`.\n- Native store uses `in-progress`.\n- `S` handler checked `BOARD_STATUSES.indexOf(task.status)`.\n- For `in-progress`, index = `-1`, so it no-op‚Äôd.\n\nFixed:\n-‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"it appers the board 'cycle' backwards is not working properly?  When I'm on an 'in-progress' task and type 'S' I expect‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:31:53.676Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5fm3fs_ce2226b955b1":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5fm3fs_ce2226b955b1","importance":5,"narrative":"cycling forward seems to throw an error?  I was on a 'Ready' task and typed 's' and was presented with an error. | Likely same root cause, opposite direction.\n\nWhat happened:\n- Board status: `in_progress`\n- Store/daemon status: `in-progress`\n- Before fix, forward cycle from `ready` sent `in_progress`.\n- Daemon rejects that enum; expects `in-progress`.\n- So `s` on Ready showed error.\n\nFix status:\n‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","subtitle":"cycling forward seems to throw an error?  I was on a 'Ready' task and typed 's' and was presented with an error.","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:35:06.853Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-07T22-14-24-749Z_019ea426-c4ed-7545-86e4-80cf4b23de8f","type":"compressed"},"obs_mq5frsc9_00bca2922758":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mq5frsc9_00bca2922758","importance":5,"narrative":"why wasn't a repo assessment done on @./fulfillment-web/ | Cause: `$ralph` queue gap.\n\nEvidence:\n- `fulfillment-web/.git` exists.\n- `fulfillment-web/docs/assessment/` has only `team-*` files.\n- No `fulfillment-web-2026-06-08.md`.\n- No misplaced `fulfillment-web-2026-06-08*.md` anywhere.\n- Original repo loop queued 10 repos but finished after **9 iterations** with queue empty.\n\nMost likely:\n- `ful‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-08T13-24-14-927Z_019ea767-bfcf-77f8-ad4b-ed9c79a73f0d","subtitle":"why wasn't a repo assessment done on @./fulfillment-web/","timestamp":"2026-06-08T16:39:32.377Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-08T13-24-14-927Z_019ea767-bfcf-77f8-ad4b-ed9c79a73f0d","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvavhg7_206809c70918":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvavhg7_206809c70918","importance":5,"narrative":"Task: Re-review current unstaged changes for Elixir-backed worktree list after User Guide fix. Verify previous docs blocker resolved and no new blocker. Do not edit. Return PASS/FAIL actionable only.\n\n## Acceptance Contract\nAcceptance level: attested\nCompletion is not accepted from prose alone. End with a structured acceptance report.\n\nCriteria:\n- criterion-1: Return concrete findings with file p‚Ä¶","sessionId":"session","subtitle":"Task: Re-review current unstaged changes for Elixir-backed worktree list after User Guide fix. Verify previous docs blo‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:04:27.410Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"session","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvbcmft_f7f384b49c1e":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvbcmft_f7f384b49c1e","importance":5,"narrative":"how's the feature parity work going? | Good. Current state:\n\n- Safe default-Elixir parity adventure: complete ‚úÖ\n  - Final broad audit PASS.\n  - Pushed: `a8adbf50 fix: fail closed on elixir fallback gaps`.\n\n- Continued native parity beyond guards:\n  - Implemented Elixir-backed `foreman worktree list` ‚úÖ\n  - `worktree clean` remains legacy-only guarded.\n  - Pushed: `7fc26863 feat: list worktrees fro‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"how's the feature parity work going?","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:17:47.029Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvbi5ko_40e242829887":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvbi5ko_40e242829887","importance":5,"narrative":"I've been using cmux but am going to switch back to using wezterm primarily because keymaps and splits work differently in cmux.  I have a few questions, is there a better session manager than tmuxinator?  I'd like to be able to use 'templates' for different project types and map templates to directories?  What other plugins should I consider to enhance my tmux experience? | Yes. Best modern stac‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c