tly legacy-only:\n  - mutating `run`, `stop`, `reset`, `merge`, `worktree clean`, purge, doctor `--fix`\n  - legacy-only `daemon`, `run task`, `sling`, `pr`, bare `plan`, sentinel run/start/st‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"continue","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:08:37.815Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvfrjjn_22c1ec2eeb59":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvfrjjn_22c1ec2eeb59","importance":5,"narrative":"continue | Continued audit.\n\nResult:\n- Broad parity audit already PASS.\n- Remaining guarded surfaces are intended:\n  - destructive/mutating legacy paths\n  - legacy-only integrations/workflows\n  - metrics cost filters requiring legacy task store\n\nNo next safe parity slice found.\nCleaned recurring `data/stream_store/*` noise.\n\nRepo state:\n- `dev` == `origin/dev`\n- working tree clean.","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"continue","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:21:21.567Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvfuf95_4cb76102b579":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvfuf95_4cb76102b579","importance":5,"narrative":"how do we 'test' this? | Test in 4 layers.\n\n### 1. Static/build gate\n\n```bash\ngit status --short\nnpx tsc --noEmit\nnpm run build\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n### 2. Targeted unit/subprocess tests\n\nRun all parity-related tests:\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run -c vitest.unit.config.ts \\\n  src/cli/__tests__/elixir-legacy-guards.test.ts \\\n  src/cli/__tests__/stop.test.ts \\\n  src/cli/__tests__/worktree.test.ts \\\n  sr‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"how do we 'test' this?","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:23:35.984Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvg31nn_68f6e4ee2aae":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvg31nn_68f6e4ee2aae","importance":5,"narrative":"how do I 'use' the new tmux features? | Use after deploy:\n\n```bash\njust deploy\n```\n\nThen restart tmux or reload:\n\n```bash\nPrefix r\n```\n\n## Main new flow\n\n### Pick project + auto-template\n\n```text\nPrefix f\n```\n\nThis opens fuzzy project picker from zoxide.\n\nPick dir. It will:\n\n1. switch to existing tmux session if present\n2. else detect project type\n3. create tmuxp layout\n\nDetection:\n\n```text\n.tmux‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c","subtitle":"how do I 'use' the new tmux features?","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:30:18.271Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvg9l70_bbf29cdc5241":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvg9l70_bbf29cdc5241","importance":5,"narrative":"oh-my-zsh DISABLE_AUTO_TITLE not set.\nPlease set:\n    export DISABLE_AUTO_TITLE='true'\nin ~/.zshrc or where your zsh profile is stored.\nRemember the \"export\" at the beginning!\nThen create a new shell or type:\n    $ source ~/.zshrc\n'dir=\"$(zoxide query -l | fzf-tmux -p 80%,70% --prompt=\"project> \")\" && ~/.local/bin/tmux-template \"$dir\"' returned 1 | Fixed + pushed.\n\nCommit: `36ccaba fix(tmux): har‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c","subtitle":"oh-my-zsh DISABLE_AUTO_TITLE not set.\nPlease set:\n    export DISABLE_AUTO_TITLE='true'\nin ~/.zshrc or where your zsh pr‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:35:23.530Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvgcfqt_c290a2bd56fc":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvgcfqt_c290a2bd56fc","importance":5,"narrative":"/loop until all tests pass without errors | Loop complete. All CI tests pass.\n\nRan:\n- `npm run test:ci` ‚úÖ\n  - unit: 302 files, 4107 tests pass\n  - integration: 38 files, 599 tests pass\n  - e2e smoke: pass\n  - e2e full-run: pass\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` ‚úÖ\n- `npm run build` ‚úÖ\n- `git diff --check` ‚úÖ\n\nFixes pushed:\n- `a57349a0 test: stabilize legacy backend suites`\n\nRepo clean:\n- `dev` == `origin/dev`\n- ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"/loop until all tests pass without errors","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:37:36.420Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvge8lm_0739621ccea3":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvge8lm_0739621ccea3","importance":5,"narrative":"[tmux-which-key] Rebuilding menu ...\n/Users/ldangelo/.local/share/tmux/plugins/tmux-which-key/init.tmux:66: command set-option: too many arguments (need at most 2)\n'/nix/store/475km4qiq3dq1a9bgyvz6lp4ipr2cvdh-tmuxplugin-tmux-which-key-0-unstable-2024-06-08/share/tmux-plugins/tmux-which-key/plugin.sh.tmux' returned 1 | Fixed live + pushed.\n\nCause:\n- `tmux-which-key/init.tmux` got copied read-only ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c","subtitle":"[tmux-which-key] Rebuilding menu ...\n/Users/ldangelo/.local/share/tmux/plugins/tmux-which-key/init.tmux:66: command set‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:39:00.487Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-26T19-19-11-824Z_019f055f-2ed0-717c-bbd6-09d0acb15d9c","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwftr70_0e01fb5b586f":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwftr70_0e01fb5b586f","importance":5,"narrative":"what's next for testing? | Next testing tiers:\n\n1. **Manual Elixir smoke**\n   - Start server:\n     - `foreman server start`\n   - Run:\n     - `foreman status`\n     - `foreman runs`\n     - `foreman metrics`\n     - `foreman metrics --compact`\n     - `foreman worktree list`\n     - `foreman worktree clean --dry-run`\n     - `foreman stop --list`\n     - `foreman stop --dry-run`\n     - `foreman run --dry‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what's next for testing?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:10:50.982Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwfxqhc_da68ee15e155":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwfxqhc_da68ee15e155","importance":5,"narrative":"foreman doctor dumps json?  Should we have a --raw/json flag that shows this but have a more human friendly output as the default? | Yes.\n\nCurrent state:\n- `foreman doctor --json` already exists.\n- But default Elixir path still prints:\n  - `Elixir server doctor: PASS`\n  - then raw JSON body\n- That‚Äôs bad default UX.\n\nBetter contract:\n- `foreman doctor` = human summary, default.\n- `foreman doctor -‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"foreman doctor dumps json?  Should we have a --raw/json flag that shows this but have a more human friendly output as t‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:13:56.663Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg3cuc_46f9f38bd96b":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg3cuc_46f9f38bd96b","importance":5,"narrative":"do it? | Done + pushed.\n\nCommit:\n- `d5a07f9b feat: render elixir doctor summary`\n\nChanged:\n- `foreman doctor` default Elixir output now human summary.\n- Added `foreman doctor --raw`.\n- `--json` still emits machine-readable JSON.\n- Docs updated.\n\nValidated:\n- `npm run test:unit -- src/cli/commands/__tests__/doctor-elixir.test.ts`\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`\n- `npm run build`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nRepo cl‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"do it?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:18:18.926Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg5810_6239c7c64701":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg5810_6239c7c64701","importance":5,"narrative":"foreman doctor lists 'provider adaptors' and 'integrations'.  What are these used for? | They‚Äôre Elixir backend health checks for two extension boundaries.\n\n- **Provider adapters**\n  - Worker execution backends.\n  - Today: mainly `pi_sdk`.\n  - Used when Elixir starts a worker phase via `WorkerProtocol.start_phase(...)`.\n  - Validates:\n    - requested provider exists\n    - provider is production-r‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"foreman doctor lists 'provider adaptors' and 'integrations'.  What are these used for?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:19:46.012Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg7bp3_5aff1865ced8":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg7bp3_5aff1865ced8","importance":5,"narrative":"give me a use case for integrations?  I get what adapters do? | Use case: **Jira ticket becomes Foreman task, once.**\n\nFlow:\n1. Jira webhook fires: issue moved to `Ready for Dev`.\n2. Integration sends command to Foreman:\n   - ‚Äúcreate task for Jira issue PROJ-123‚ÄĚ\n   - includes dedupe key: `jira:PROJ-123:ready-for-dev`\n3. Elixir records event:\n   - `IntegrationCommandIngested`\n4. Projection stores‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"give me a use case for integrations?  I get what adapters do?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:21:24.084Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg8g5l_bc20256ff666":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg8g5l_bc20256ff666","importance":5,"narrative":"Ah, so in the case of Jira do task updates get written back to Jira? | Planned/partial, not full native loop yet.\n\nCurrent intent:\n- Jira can be an external task source/status surface.\n- Foreman should ingest Jira events into Elixir, dedupe them, create/link tasks.\n- Foreman should eventually emit updates back:\n  - task status changes\n  - run started/completed/failed\n  - comments with report link‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"Ah, so in the case of Jira do task updates get written back to Jira?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:22:16.517Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwganjs_480a84014ee6":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwganjs_480a84014ee6","importance":5,"narrative":"Not in beads, use foreman's native tasks | Added native Foreman task.\n\n- ID: `52ba0d80-913d-4880-871b-a81e308c34d4-2c7da`\n- Title: `Add native Jira write-back integration`\n- Status: `backlog`\n- Priority: low\n\nCovers:\n- Jira-linked task status write-back\n- run started/completed/failed comments\n- blocker/needs-operator state sync\n- report/PR links\n- dedupe/audit events\n- native Elixir path, legacy ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"Not in beads, use foreman's native tasks","time