72473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhcy4w_3297c30def24":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhcy4w_3297c30def24","importance":5,"narrative":"can you build it? | Built + pushed.\n\nCommit:\n- `9ed23352 test: add elixir critical path e2e`\n\nNew command:\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e:elixir\n```\n\nAlso included in:\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e\nnpm run test:ci\n```\n\nCovers:\n- isolated Elixir server\n- doctor human/JSON\n- metrics compact\n- project registration\n- task create/approve/list/show\n- scheduler claim\n- runs/status/logs\n- worktree/stop/reset/purge ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"can you build it?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:53:46.048Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhnk38_c2deecfd9f3c":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhnk38_c2deecfd9f3c","importance":5,"narrative":"there's literally only one elixir test? | Yep. Bad shape.\n\nFixed: split into 6 Elixir E2E tests in same lane:\n\n- server status + health\n- doctor + metrics\n- task create/approve/list/show\n- scheduler claim\n- read-only operator views\n- fail-closed legacy guards\n\nValidated:\n- `npm run test:e2e:elixir` ‚úÖ ‚ÄĒ now `6 passed`\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` ‚úÖ\n- `git diff --check` ‚úÖ\n\nAmended + pushed:\n- `1d007928 tes‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"there's literally only one elixir test?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:02:01.058Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhx9n8_c14d9ebf46e5":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhx9n8_c14d9ebf46e5","importance":5,"narrative":"what exactly is being tested by the elixir tests? | Elixir E2E lane tests one shared isolated Elixir server + temp project.\n\nFile:\n- `src/integration/__tests__/elixir-critical-path.e2e.test.ts`\n\nCommand:\n- `npm run test:e2e:elixir`\n\nTests:\n\n1. **Server health/status**\n   - starts `packages/foreman_server` via `mix run --no-halt`\n   - waits for HTTP health\n   - runs `foreman server status --port 4‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what exactly is being tested by the elixir tests?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:09:34.073Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhy6lr_ef3ebb959d8e":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhy6lr_ef3ebb959d8e","importance":5,"narrative":"what so run is still using node? | Yes ‚ÄĒ **plain `foreman run` is still legacy Node-only** in default Elixir mode.\n\nCurrent contract:\n\n- `foreman run` ‚Üí **blocked/fails closed** in Elixir mode.\n- `foreman run --dry-run` ‚Üí Elixir projection-backed preview.\n- Actual execution path should be:\n  - start Elixir server/scheduler: `foreman server start`\n  - create/approve tasks via native task commands\n‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what so run is still using node?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:10:16.785Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwi0a32_7a37a51bc58d":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwi0a32_7a37a51bc58d","importance":5,"narrative":"isn't the primary purpose of elixir to use event sourcing?  meaning run would no longer be 'blind' to what the run is doing?? | Yes. Correct.\n\nPrimary Elixir purpose:\n- event-sourced command ingestion\n- projections for task/run/operator state\n- scheduler decisions from projections\n- run lifecycle emitted as events\n- CLI/operator views no longer blind/stale/local-file based\n\nCurrent problem:\n- **E‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"isn't the primary purpose of elixir to use event sourcing?  meaning run would no longer be 'blind' to what the run is d‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:11:54.627Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwi1qm9_8f89644d30c8":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwi1qm9_8f89644d30c8","importance":5,"narrative":"what else is still using the legacy backend? | Yes. Still legacy / Node-gated today:\n\n## Fully legacy-only commands/paths\n\nRequire `FOREMAN_BACKEND=node`:\n\n- `foreman run` actual dispatch\n- `foreman run task ...` direct worker bridge\n- `foreman daemon start|stop|status|restart`\n- `foreman pr`\n- `foreman sling ...`\n- default `foreman plan <description>` PRD‚ÜíTRD pipeline\n  - Elixir alternatives: `f‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what else is still using the legacy backend?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:13:02.696Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwi7hzn_b95141cb61c7":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwi7hzn_b95141cb61c7","importance":5,"narrative":"Task: Inspect Elixir server modules for commands/events/projections already available for run dispatch, stop/reset/worktree cleanup/purge/merge/pr/plan/sling/issue/sentinel. Identify what can be wired now vs needs new Elixir implementation. Do not edit files.\n\n## Acceptance Contract\nAcceptance level: attested\nCompletion is not accepted from prose alone. End with a structured acceptance report.\n\nC‚Ä¶","sessionId":"session","subtitle":"Task: Inspect Elixir server modules for commands/events/projections already available for run dispatch, stop/reset/work‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:17:31.462Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"session","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwi7xi5_100723b8ee4e":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwi7xi5_100723b8ee4e","importance":5,"narrative":"Task: Audit the Foreman repo for remaining legacy Node backend command paths gated by FOREMAN_BACKEND=node. Produce a prioritized replacement plan with exact files/functions and current Elixir API/projection gaps. Do not edit files.\n\n## Acceptance Contract\nAcceptance level: attested\nCompletion is not accepted from prose alone. End with a structured acceptance report.\n\nCriteria:\n- criterion-1: Ret‚Ä¶","sessionId":"session","subtitle":"Task: Audit the Foreman repo for remaining legacy Node backend command paths gated by FOREMAN_BACKEND=node. Produce a p‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:17:51.569Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"session","type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwjdu0l_3a7abff5c88c":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwjdu0l_3a7abff5c88c","importance":5,"narrative":"/loop until all legacy backend code is replaced with elixir, implement e2e tests, stop when all node backend code is replaced with elixir and all e2e tests pass.  Don't stop until complete.  Once complete delete the node backend implementations. | Progress pushed. Not complete yet.\n\nDone now:\n- `302fa074 feat: route run through elixir scheduler`\n  - `foreman run` now ticks Elixir scheduler.\n  - n‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"/loop until all legacy backend code is replaced with elixir, implement e2e tests, stop when all node backend code is re‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:50:26.610Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-7